headlines.description: — Joel Embiid declined at first to wear a “ Big Energy ” chain before he reluctantly agreed to slip on the gaudy necklace and flexed his muscles for a quick photo at his locker.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid returns with seventh career triple-double in 76ers' rout of Chicago Bulls

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 26 points, 10 assists and a fourth-quarter dunk over Victor Wembanyama, Desmond Bane added 24 points and the Memphis Grizzlies used a second-half spurt to beat the San...
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 26, dunks on Wembanyama as Grizzlies pull away from Spurs for a 106-98 win

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Pelicans coach Willie Green sounds gratified by the way his surging New Orleans squad seems to be building chemistry and momentum. Brooklyn coach Jacque Vaughn wants the Nets to summon the kind of hustle that shows they actually care about winning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans roll to wire-to-wire, lopsided victory over reeling Nets

events.name: Boston Celtics at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — That's another signature win for the Oklahoma City Thunder.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 36 as Thunder top league-leading Celtics for 5th straight win

events.name: Orlando Magic at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 36 points and delivered on key plays in the fourth quarter to help the Golden State Warriors snap a three-game losing streak with a 121-115 victory over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 36 points to lead the Warriors past the Magic 121-115

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 14 of his 34 points in the fourth quarter after missing a game due to illness, and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Sacramento Kings 111-104 on Tuesday night to snap an 11-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier scores 34 in return from illness, Hornets beat Kings 111-104 to snap 11-game skid
